## Values and Principles
*Core. Unchanging. Not associated with a project, area, or task. Can be used to arbitrate between conflicting tasks or areas.*

### Stop and Smell the Pine Trees Along the Way
It's not that serious. The point of life may be to "make cool stuff, see cool stuff, share cool stuff, and die."

### Make Cool Stuff
One of the best ways we can contribute to the world is to produce stuff that makes it better. It doesn't have to be huge, or adored by many, it just needs to be real and have a positive impact. Make things that makes others feel the way your favorite things make you feel.

### Mise En Place
Having "everything in place" is a superpower that makes everything else easier. This doesn't mean get bogged down in "clearing the decks" before doing any meaningful work. It means that slowing down and fully understanding, parsing, and synthesizing is the best way to be effective, feel in control, and enjoy your life and work.

### Know Thyself
It's always worth investing in understanding what you want and need from life as well as how your current strategies are working to achieve that. People generally underinvest in self-knowledge and it's return on investment is enormous.

### Integrity
Don’t “hedge your bets” and make sure that you allow other people their full agency by being clear, brave, and honest with them. Essentially act in a way that allows you to maintain "fuck you money" (in all ways, not just money). "Acting with integrity isn't something you do in the moment, it's the consequences of a lot of good forward-looking decisions."


